==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sulphydrate
<hw>Sul*phy"drate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A compound, analogous to a hydrate, regarded as a salt of
sulphydric acid, or as a derivative of hydrogen sulphide in which one
half of the hydrogen is replaced by a base (as potassium
<xex>sulphydrate</xex>, <chform>KSH</chform>), or as a hydrate in which
the oxygen has been wholly or partially replaced by sulphur.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sulphydric</ent>⟦br⟧
